Murakami and Nakabayashi are just policemen trying to do their jobs. When there is a bomb explosion inside Shuei Primary School, they are asked to do their jobs as policemen and check out the lead. It turns out a doctor from a mental institution called in to warn about the explosion immediately before the bomb went off. And so begins their association with the nameless mental patient whom they would eventually call &quot;Maki.&quot;
For some reason, Maki can &quot;speak&quot; with spirits. There are spirits all around us, and Maki can communicate with them. These spirits tell Maki about deep dark things... things that go on when no one else is looking...

(From Selene Scans)

Hirano Yukito is at the end of his rope.  He's decided to kill himself - all he needs is just one more little push.  But things don't always go the way you think they will... Semi-finalist for Afternoon's Spring 2016 Four Seasons Award.

[b][u]French/Fran&ccedil;ais[/u][/b]
Hirano Yukito ne supporte plus de vivre. Il d&eacute;cide de mettre fin &agrave; sa vie &ndash; et n&rsquo;attend plus qu&rsquo;un signe pour sauter le pas. Mais les choses se passent rarement telles qu&rsquo;on le souhaiterait&hellip;

Huang Bei Yue is an assassin that gets transported to another world thanks to a mysterious jade, boundless beast!
Now she resides in the body of a 12 year old, who happens to be the king's sister, who is constantly bullied!
&quot;Now how shall i take my revenge?&quot;
